values: 礼堂；会堂；大厅；门厅；走廊；过道；（大学或学院里的）教学楼；学生宿舍；（大学中的）公共食堂；办公楼；会所；乡村庄园；府邸；庄园；（Hall）霍尔（人名）

synonym.mean: 门厅，走廊；会堂；食堂；学生宿舍

市府办公大楼, 市政厅
歌舞杂耍表演；歌舞杂耍剧场

bilingual.target: 它们让大厅看起来很漂亮。
是什么让大厅看起来很棒？
我们在大厅里看着一切。

bilingual.source: The silence in the hall is still and deep.
bilingual.target: 大厅里的寂静依然深沉。

bilingual.source: There is a hall behind the classroom building.
bilingual.target: 教学楼后面有一个大厅。

bilingual.source: Tchang found himself in a mighty hall.
bilingual.target: 昌发现自己在一个宏伟的大厅里。

bilingual.source: Look! That's the tallest dinosaur in this hall.
bilingual.target: 看！那是这个大厅里最高的恐龙。

bilingual.source: I stand there in the silence and look around the hall.
bilingual.target: 我站在那儿，静静地环顾大厅。

list.abstract: hall是一种室内场馆，属于一个大型场所中的一部分，它除了可以召开演唱会外，还可以组织其它各种会议活动，比较出名的有大阪城HALL、NHK HALL和东京国际FORUM HALL等。
hall是一个英语单词，可以用作名词，可以翻译为过道、走廊，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: Where's this little party? Yeah, whatever, hi, I don't care. Greenwich hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在哪儿举办？无所谓我又不在乎。格林威治大厅。

yingyinNormal.en: Wow. How do you get an entire lecture hall to flip you off at the same time?
yingyinNormal.zh: 哇，你要怎么做才能让整个演讲大厅里的人同时冲你竖中指啊？

yingyinNormal.en: And I'd planned for music later on. And maybe a bit of a hoolie. None of which would be suitable in the Great Hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我还打算稍后来点音乐，大家玩玩闹闹，但这些都不适合在大厅做。

yingyinNormal.en: And you passed them in the hall? And Will was on his phone? Yeah. He left me a voice mail on my phone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在大厅里遇到了他们？当时威尔正在打电话？是的。他给我留了一条语音信息。

yingyinNormal.en: Welcome to the Hall of Heroism.
yingyinNormal.zh: 欢迎来到英雄的殿堂。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait in the hall while I change.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我换件衣服，你在走廊等着。

yingyinNormal.en: This is ridiculous. I'm going across the hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这实在太荒唐了，我要去对面屋待一会。

yingyinNormal.en: Wow. This is way nicer than my Hall of Wimpiness.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我住的地方跟这一比简直是个土坑。

yingyinNormal.en: Joey, there is a perfectly good couch across the hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊，走廊对面有很好的沙发。

yingyinNormal.en: By the way, this didn't seem so dorky out in the hall. Come on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对了，刚才在外面排演没这么蠢的。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, we did get dressed up and come all the way to City Hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实呢，我们都穿戴整齐了而且大老远来到了市政厅。

yingyinNormal.en: It's only for five weeks. Yeah, and we'll be right across the hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只是同住五周而已。而且我们俩就在对门而已。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello? Wow. Hi. Yes, I'm sorry the models are actually down the hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗨。嗨，对不起，模特儿面试在走廊尽头的办公室。

yingyinNormal.en: We wish to partake of this information from your great hall of wisdom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们希望从您伟大的智慧殿堂里获得一些信息。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you doing in the girls' hall? I was actually looking for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在女生楼里干嘛呢？实际上，我在找你。

yingyinNormal.en: And then, Raj, you bring the stuff across the hall and start setting up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然后拉杰，你把东西搬到对面，然后开始布置。

yingyinNormal.en: Is the Hall of Fragrance suitable to your comfort? Yes, it is most pleasing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不知芬芳亭是否合你的意？那里非常舒适。

yingyinNormal.en: Funny, because I was just gonna go across the hall and write that on Chandler.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有意思，我正想到对面在钱德身上那样写。

yingyinNormal.en: Uh-huh. And you are? Penny, I live across the hall. I've heard a lot about you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是，你是？佩妮，我就住对门，我听说了你很多事情。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, come on guys, it's not like I moved to Europe. I just moved across the hall.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别这样，我又不是搬去欧洲，我只是搬到对面。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The switch from classroom to lecture <highlight>hall</highlight> is not an inevitable one and that other options are available.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从教室到演讲厅的转换不是不可避免的，还有其他选择。

examination_example.sentence: Drunks, tramps, and music <highlight>hall</highlight> performers might gurn and grin with a smile as wide as Lewis Carroll's gum-exposing Cheshire Cat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 醉汉、流浪汉和音乐厅的表演者可能会咧着嘴笑，笑得像刘易斯·卡罗尔的露出牙龈的柴郡猫一样。

examination_example.sentence: It's as if you're driving a stick shift, says Judith <highlight>Hall</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 朱迪思·霍尔说：“这就好像你在开手动档车。”

examination_example.sentence: Judith <highlight>Hall</highlight> mentions driving to show that reflection can be distracting.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 朱迪思·霍尔提到开车是为了证明思考会分散注意力。
